{
  "name": "20g Protein Frosted Cookies",
  "description": "Macro-friendly frosted protein cookie (Instagram) ingested as a crumbl base-chassis candidate. Notable for a claimed <10 kcal per g protein, achieved by protein-loading: 3 scoops whey in only 5 cookies plus a full cup of nonfat Greek yogurt in the frosting. Modeled with regular AP flour (source said 'Bob's Red Mill GF flour or regular flour'); generic sweetener -> granulated Splenda; the 1 egg white authored as 33 g (one large white) since the library egg-white has no count equivalence; sprinkles ('to taste') omitted so it reads as a clean unfrosted-chassis sibling to the other crumbl cookies. Component keys aligned with the Birthday Cake base so compare row-aligns and promote can graft by key. Not yet made.",
  "tags": [
    "crumbl",
    "cookie",
    "protein",
    "frosted",
    "base-candidate"
  ],
